criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  early invasive BC (TNM stage I - III);

          -  diagnosed and/or treated in the AVL or UMCG;

          -  treated 5 - 7 years or 10 - 12 years ago;

          -  aged 40-50 years at time of therapy;

          -  signed written informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  history of RT or CT unrelated to BC;

          -  current treatment for BC recurrence or second malignancy (including contralateral BC)
             with the exception of non-melanoma skin cancer or curatively treated carcinoma in situ
             of the cervix;

          -  history of cardiac disease (CHF, acute coronary syndrome, coronary revascularization
             procedure, symptomatic valvular dysfunction, cardiomyopathy or congenital heart
             defect) before diagnosis and treatment for BC;

          -  mental disability or psychological condition potentially hampering compliance with the
             study protocol;

          -  insufficient understanding of the Dutch language.
